name: Claim
desc: Represents a claim requested from a credential.

name: copyWith
desc: Creates a copy of this claim with the given fields replaced with the new values.

name: id
desc: An optional identifier for this claim.

name: path
desc: The path to the claim in the credential. Must not be empty. String / int / null values are allowed.

name: toJson
desc: Converts the object to a JSON-serializable value.

name: values
desc: A list of specific values requested for this claim.

name: toJson
desc: Converts the object to a JSON-serializable value.

name: ageOver18
desc: Boolean: True if user is > 18 (Calculated by Wallet, no DOB revealed)

name: drivingPrivileges
desc: Returns a list of vehicle categories (A, B, C...) the user can drive.

name: issuingCountry
desc: Alpha-2 code (e.g., 'ES')

name: sex
desc: ISO 5218 code (1=Male, 2=Female)

name: unDistinguishingSign
desc: e.g. 'E' for Spain

name: vehicleHolder
desc:
IMPORTANT: This is a complex object identifying the owner.
However, the actual human name (family_name) usually lives
in the borrowed 'org.iso.18013.5.1' namespace.

name: Credential
desc: Represents a requested credential in a DCQL query.

name: Credential.new
desc: Format defaults to Formats.sd_jwt

name: addClaim
desc: Adds a claim to the credential and returns the updated credential.

name: addClaimSet
desc: Adds a claim set to the credential and returns the updated credential.

name: claimSets
desc: A list of claim sets, where each claim set is a list of claim IDs.

name: claims
desc: A list of claims to request from the credential.

name: format
desc:
The format of the credential (e.g., mdoc, sd_jwt, etc.)
Defaults to Format.sd_jwt

name: id
desc: A unique identifier for this credential query.

name: meta
desc: Metadata about the credential, such as the document type.

name: multiple
desc: Whether multiple credentials matching this query can be returned.

name: removeClaim
desc: Removes a claim from the credential and returns the updated credential.

name: removeClaimSet
desc: Removes a claim set from the credential and returns the updated credential.

name: requireCryptographicHolderBinding
desc: Whether cryptographic holder binding is required.

name: toJson
desc: Converts the object to a JSON-serializable value.

name: trustedAuthorities
desc: A list of trusted authorities (issuers) for this credential.
Separator, returns the current builder instance.

name: claim
desc: Adds a claim to the credential.

name: claimSet
desc: Adds a claim set to the credential.

name: jwtPid
desc: Helper to set the credential type to SD-JWT PID.

name: mDL
desc: Helper to set the credential type to mDoc Driving License.

name: mVRC
desc: Helper to set the credential type to mDoc mVRC.

name: meta
desc: Sets a metadata value for the credential.

name: multiple
desc: Sets whether multiple credentials matching this query can be returned.

name: requireBinding
desc: Sets whether cryptographic holder binding is required.

name: setCredential
desc: Sets the credential type, updating the format and metadata filter.

name: trustedAuthority
desc: Adds a trusted authority (issuer) for the credential.

name: CredentialSet
desc: Defines a set of credentials that satisfy a query requirement.

name: options
desc: A list of options, where each option is a list of credential IDs.

name: required
desc: Whether this credential set is required.

name: toJson
desc: Converts the object to a JSON-serializable value.
Separator, returns the current builder instance.

name: option
desc: Adds an option to the credential set.

name: required
desc: Sets whether this credential set is required.

name: CredentialType
desc: Class for holding format / doctype relationships

name: toJson
desc: Converts the object to a JSON-serializable value.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: DcqlBuilder
desc:
Builds a DCQL query. Use the DcqlBuilder class to build a DCQL query.
Check the example directory for more examples.
Separator, returns the current builder instance.

name: build
desc:
Builds the DCQL query.
If skipValidation is false, the query will be validated before building.
Throws a ValidationException if the query is invalid.

name: credential
desc: Adds a new credential to the query.

name: credentialSet
desc: Adds a new credential set to the query.

name: query
desc: The DCQL query being built.

name: validate
desc:
Validates the current state of the query.
Returns a ValidationResult with a list of errors if invalid.

name: DcqlQuery
desc: Represents a DCQL (Digital Credentials Query Language) query.

name: addCredential
desc: Adds a credential to the query.

name: addCredentialSet
desc: Adds a credentialSet to the query.

name: credentialSets
desc: A list of credential sets that define combinations of credentials that satisfy the query.

name: credentials
desc: A list of credentials to request.

name: removeCredential
desc: Removes a credential from the query.

name: removeCredentialSet
desc: Removes a credentialSet from the query.

name: toJson
desc: Converts the object to a JSON-serializable value.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: FieldValidator
desc: A helper class for defining field validators.

name: ValidationException
desc: An exception thrown when a DCQL query is invalid.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: ValidationResult
desc: The result of a DCQL query validation.

name: ValidationResult.invalid
desc: Creates an invalid result with a list of errors.

name: ValidationResult.valid
desc: Creates a valid result.

name: contextPath
desc: The path to the invalid field (e.g., query.credentials[0].id).

name: errors
desc: A list of error messages if the validation failed.

name: isInvalid
desc: Returns true if the validation failed.

name: isValid
desc: Returns true if the validation passed.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.

name: DcqlValidator
desc: Validates a DCQL query against the specification.

name: validate
desc: Validates a DcqlQuery object.

name: validateJson
desc: Validates a JSON string representing a DCQL query.

name: toJson
desc: Converts the object to a JSON-serializable value.

name: toString
desc: A string representation of this object.
